<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-453-428  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 453 428.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  May 14 1990 v9 n10 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Government gets OS/2 document retrieval system. (Topic system fromVerity Inc.) (Topic 1.2)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taft, Darryl K.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Topic 2.0 (Data base management system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Government AgencyData Base Management SystemsOS-2Information Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Government Gets OS/2 Document Retrieval SystemandM;Verity Inc. officials said government customers were among the first to getthe new OS/2 version of the company's Topic document retrieval system.andM;The first shipments of Verity's Topic OS/2 product went to key customers inthe government, specifically in the intelligence community, officials of theMountain View, Calif., company said.andP;  They would not be more specific.andM;Company officials said Topic represents the next generation in documentretrieval systems, offering end users the most comprehensive text and imagesearch and retrieval capabilities available today.andP;  Topic is based on conceptretrieval technology, an easy-to-use method that uses a knowledge base oftopics.andM;The Topic architecture supports retrievals across large collections ofdocuments stored in multiple formats on diverse computing platforms.andP;  Theproduct is designed for distributed network computing environments, and itoptimizes all computing resources on a network, resulting in very fastretrievals, the officials said.andM;&quot;The need to effectively search and access information from corporatedatabases and real-time data sources is critical in both mainstream businessand government environments,&quot; said Michael S. Pliner, president and chiefexecutive officer of Verity.andM;Topic consists of the Topic Retrieval Client and the Topic Database Builder,and runs on networked servers and mixed retrieval MS-DOS and OS/2 clients.andM;Topic supports the major file sharing network products from companies such asNovell Inc., 3Com Corp. and IBM Corp.andP;  Topic is document-format-independent,supports most major word processing and desktop publishing packages, and alsosupports image formats, company officials said.andM;Initial Topic applications based on OS/2 include policies and proceduresmanagement, sales and technical support in information management, real-timeinformation profiling for opportunity and risk assessment, and litigationsupport and case analysis, company officials said.andM;Topic capabilities for the OS/2 version include support for real-timeinformation source; HyperLink connections to images, annotations anddocuments; the Topic-By-Example query builder; and the optional TopicSQL-Bridge interface to OS/2 and Structured Query Language relationaldatabase management systems such as Oracle Corp.'s Oracle Server andMicrosoft Corp.'s SQL Server.andM;Topic Version 1.2 is available under OS/2 standard and extended editions for80286 and 80386 machines.andM;A typical Topic OS/2 configuration, with an OS/2 server supporting up to 10users, costs less than $25,000, company officials said.andM;Contact Robert Williams at Verity, tel.andP;  415-960-7600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>